n\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533555\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533555\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 30, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104wvm1665703133337.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wvm1665703133337.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wvm1665703133337.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"wvm1665703133337\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"wvm1665703133337__ugetregs_403818\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Get the string value of a Uniface general variable ($1 ... $99).</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"wvm1665703133337__topic_d120587e1_d120588e1_d120589e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104wvm1665703133337_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"wvm1665703133337__codeblock_es1_sn1_1wb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">long ugetregs (shortnum, unsigned char*buffer, shortmax);</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wvm1665703133337__topic_d85742e1_d85743e1_d85744e1_d85745e1_d85746e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d136441e61\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"wvm1665703133337__parml_il3_tn1_1wb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">num</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Number of the Uniface general variable. Allowed values are 1 through 99.</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">buffer</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Contents of the general variable (Output).</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">max</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Maximum size of the string data to be retrieved. Because the buffer must also\n                  hold the zero terminator, the length of the buffer pointed to by\n                     <var class=\"keyword varname\">buffer</var> must be at least <var class=\"keyword varname\">max</var>+1 bytes. The\n                  maximum value you can specify here is 32,766.</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wvm1665703133337__topic_d85747e1_d85748e1_d85749e1_d85750e1_d85751e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d136441e106\">Return Values</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wvm1665703133337__p_d120608e1_d120609e1_d120610e1\">The number of bytes copied into <var class=\"keyword varname\">buffer</var>, not including the zero terminator. Zero is returned if the value of <var class=\"keyword varname\">num</var> is out of range.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wvm1665703133337__topic_d85752e1_d85753e1_d85754e1_d85755e1_d85756e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d136441e121\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wvm1665703133337__d5947e20\">Library:  <span class=\"ph filepath\">yrtl</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wvm1665703133337__topic_d85757e1_d85758e1_d85759e1_d85760e1_d85761e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d136441e134\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wvm1665703133337__p_d120620e1_d120621e1_d120622e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">ugetregs</code> copies a maximum of\n               <var class=\"keyword varname\">max</var> bytes of string data from the specified general variable\n               <var class=\"keyword varname\">num</var> to <var class=\"keyword varname\">buffer</var>, adding a zero terminator after\n            the last byte. The zero terminator is always written, even if you did not copy all of\n            the contents of the general register. Trailing spaces are not removed.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wvm1665703133337__p_d120623e1_d120624e1_d120625e1\">The length of <var class=\"keyword varname\">buffer</var> should be\n            at least <var class=\"keyword varname\">max</var>+1 bytes. <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugetregs</code> can transfer a\n            maximum of 32,767 bytes in total, even if you put a higher value in the\n               <var class=\"keyword varname\">max</var> parameter. If you need to transfer more data, you should\n            consider transferring the data from a field, instead of from a general variable, using\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufget</code> in combination with <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufgetc</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wvm1665703133337__p_d120626e1_d120627e1_d120628e1\">If the data in the variable contains information\n            that is not in Font 0, ‘shift font’ characters appear in the string.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wvm1665703133337__p_d120629e1_d120630e1_d120631e1\">Profile and subfield characters, if present in a\n            field, are also returned in the buffer, so you should be prepared to handle these. For\n            information about the representation of these characters, refer to the \"Subfield\n            Separator and Profile Characters\" topic.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wvm1665703133337__section_g1q_l41_1wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d136441e182\">ProcScript</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following example retrieves and prints the string value of general\n            register <code class=\"ph codeph\">$10</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104wvm1665703133337_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"wvm1665703133337__codeblock_u2c_j41_1wb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$10 = \"abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz\"\nperform \"GETREG10\"\n$10 = \"12345 \"\nperform \"GETREG10\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wvm1665703133337__section_rk4_m41_1wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d136441e197\">3GL code</h2>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104wvm1665703133337_html_2\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"wvm1665703133337__codeblock_mlb_441_1wb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#include &lt;h3gl.h&gt;\n\nEXPORT void GETREG10 ()\n{\nchar value[21];\nlong len;\n\nlen = ugetregs(10, value, 20);\nprintf(\"Length = %d, Value is : '%s'\\n\", len, value);\n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">The following example prints out these lines:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104wvm1665703133337_html_3\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"wvm1665703133337__codeblock_mry_p41_1wb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">Length = 20, Value is : 'abcdefghijklmnopqrst'\nLength = 6, Value is : '12345 '</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pan1665702658270.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Subfield Separator and Profile Characters</a><p>Uniface uses part of the reserved area of each meta character set (that is, the first 32 characters plus the last character) to store characters with special meaning within Uniface, such as subfield separators and profile characters.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jqk1665703133137.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ugetreg</a><p>Get the integer value of a Uniface general variable ($1 ... $99).</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wyf1665703133267.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ugetregf</a><p>Get the double-precision value of a Uniface general variable ($1 ... $99).</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wrj1665703133411.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uputreg</a><p>Copy a long integer value into the specified general variable ($1 ... $99).</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533555\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533555\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "ugetregs Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 30, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Get the string value of a Uniface general variable ($1 ... $99). Explain this code long ugetregs (shortnum, unsigned char*buffer, shortmax); Copy Parameters num Number of the Uniface general variable. Allowed values are 1 through 99. buffer Contents of the general variable (Output). max Maximum size of the string data to be retrieved. Because the buffer must also hold the zero terminator, the length of the buffer pointed to by buffer must be at least max +1 bytes. The maximum value you can specify here is 32,766. Return Values The number of bytes copied into buffer , not including the zero terminator. Zero is returned if the value of num is out of range. Use Library: yrtl Description ugetregs copies a maximum of max bytes of string data from the specified general variable num to buffer , adding a zero terminator after the last byte. The zero terminator is always written, even if you did not copy all of the contents of the general register. Trailing spaces are not removed. The length of buffer should be at least max +1 bytes. ugetregs can transfer a maximum of 32,767 bytes in total, even if you put a higher value in the max parameter. If you need to transfer more data, you should consider transferring the data from a field, instead of from a general variable, using ufget in combination with ufgetc . If the data in the variable contains information that is not in Font 0, ‘shift font’ characters appear in the string. Profile and subfield characters, if present in a field, are also returned in the buffer, so you should be prepared to handle these. For information about the representation of these characters, refer to the \"Subfield Separator and Profile Characters\" topic. ProcScript The following example retrieves and prints the string value of general register $10 : Explain this code $10 = \"abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz\" perform \"GETREG10\" $10 = \"12345 \" perform \"GETREG10\" Copy 3GL code Explain this code #include <h3gl.h> EXPORT void GETREG10 () { char value[21]; long len; len = ugetregs(10, value, 20); printf(\"Length = %d, Value is : '%s'\\n\", len, value); } Copy The following example prints out these lines: Explain this code Length = 20, Value is : 'abcdefghijklmnopqrst' Length = 6, Value is : '12345 ' Copy Related Links Subfield Separator and Profile Characters Uniface uses part of the reserved area of each meta character set (that is, the first 32 characters plus the last character) to store characters with special meaning within Uniface, such as subfield separators and profile characters. ugetreg Get the integer value of a Uniface general variable ($1 ... $99). ugetregf Get the double-precision value of a Uniface general variable ($1 ... $99). uputreg Copy a long integer value into the specified general variable ($1 ... $99). Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}